{"word":"ἀρνίον","slug":"ἀρνίον","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἀρνίον, ου, τό</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀρήν\">ἀρήν</a></el>] diminutive of <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀρήν\">ἀρήν</a></el>, but later a sheep of any age, in <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ NT\">NT</a> only in imagery <b><i>lamb, sheep</i></b> of Christ <b><a href='B:730 5:6'>Rv 5:6</a></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ al.\">al.</a>; of members of the Christian community<b> <a href='B:500 21:15'>J 21:15</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:Ἀρνί\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀρνῶν\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}